comments.body:
@Kihwal
I think that case can actually be handled.  {{IOUtils.copyBytes}}, even when passed the close-stream flag, does not appear to reliably close the streams...  The {{try}} block that deletes the temp file can also close the stream if it's open.

@Todd
I think is actually an issue {{FileSystem}} since {{FsShell}} doesn't get a chance to cleanup when SIGINT blows it out of the water.  The FS shutdown hook is going to delete all temp files (ie. copy in progress file), and then call {{DFSClient#close}} which will close the stream to the temp file after it has been deleted.  Trying to do signal handling in java seems a bit messy, so may the shutdown hook behavior could be modified.
